ong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Miss di Palearia was born about 1155, in Italy, her father, Pietro di Palearia, was 32 and her mother, Letitia di Manoppello, was 27. She had at least 1 son with Pietro di Celano."},"et":{"about 1155–":"umbes 1155–Surnud","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1159–1212":"1159–1212","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1159":"1159","1125":"1125","1212":"1212","1155":"1155","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","1183":"1183","about 1155":"umbes 1155","1182":"1182","Italy":"Itaalia"},"fi":{"about 1155–":"noin 1155–Kuollut","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1159–1212":"1159–1212","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1159":"1159","1125":"1125","1212":"1212","1155":"1155","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","1183":"1183","about 1155":"noin 1155","1182":"1182","Italy":"Italia"},"fr":{"about 1155–":"environ 1155–Décédée","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1159–1212":"1159–1212","1182–1252":"1182–1252","1125–1183":"1125–1183","1130–Female":"